<br>
1) I started out casting kei for free as a friendly gesture on passerby in the zone I was hunting in.  Ended up with a guy who stalked me every night and running to every zone I was in for kei.  Every night he'd send me a tell, &quot;Where are you?&quot;  Then he would show up, and bring his friends along for free kei.<br>
<br>
2) This girl met me in a group while we hunted one night, so she's a one-time-hunting acquaintance.  On the next night, while I was looking toward the puller, and she was not in my group, she came up with a friend and blocked my view on any possbile adds.  She had her friends with her, and they wanted free kei.<br>
<br>
They were in an uber guild.  I was afraid if I refused it would mean they would not group with me anymore.  What agony!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->         Later I saw they were selling uber gear for 80k pp.  As rich as they were, they felt interrupting me for a free kei and endangering my current group was their right.  That was when I thought: Why would I want to court the favor of these kind of people?  Do I want to be in their group?  Nah.<br>
<br>
3) Some of my friends were forming a group for LDoN, and had initially invited me.  I ran there; then they said they needed more dps, so they called their wiz friend and told me now there were too many people for the group.  I offered to leave, and they quickly accepted and asked,  &quot;Can you kei us?&quot;  That was when I decided: No more!  I would not cast on anyone but my own group.  My friends were initially upset that I would no longer cast on them, but I told them, &quot;Hey, if people are my real friends, then they wouldn't leave me out of their group while asking me for kei.&quot;<br>
<br>
4) The few nights I did cast kei for donation in PoK brought in pretty poor donations.  The max people would donate now was 50 pp.  Many would go below that, 30pp, 20pp, 8 pp, and some would walk away without donating a copper and .. yep, without even a &quot;thanks&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->         I was happy with people who gave 50 pp, but even then it was not really fun.  I much prefer hunting.  And yes, if I had a lucky time, I could win a rune word (and did), or an ornate patter (and did).  I know several people (pally, etc.) who solo on kei and make easily 50k a night.  Why do a lot of people think they should just tip the chanter 50 pp?  Oh well.  They can do what they feel is right.  But if they don't have many chanters willing to sit in PoK to cast kei, it's something they need to figure out on why.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to today.  I never cast for donation anymore. This is the choice I made.<br>
<br>
Now that I live by the rule of only casting kei on my own group, I'm being invited by people who respect my rule.  I'm happy because from all indications they are impressed by how I can do crowd control, and are not just trying to be my friend for free kei.  I'm having a great time getting multiple invites every night as I log in.<br>
<br>
Whoever titled this thread &quot;A tale of Enchanter Greed&quot; should think harder on how people treat the enchanters when it comes to asking for kei.  Bottom line is people want to have kei so they can get phat lewt and phat exp while leaving an enchanter behind.  I pay to play a game for fun, not to do public service.  If I wanted to do real public service I would be volunteering at many local charity organizations, boy scouts and schools and hospitals.  When you are in a game, please respect other people are there to have fun, not to be hounded to suit your fun. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whitlan>Whitlan</A> at: 12/23/03 11:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glaekenrasilom>GlaekenRasilom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#330000>(12/28/03 1:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=81>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A tale of Enchanter Greed...</span><hr size=1> It's been a short while since my post stating I hit 60 finally,and many changes have occured in Norrath since that post.I am lvl 62 now and have concentrated my energy towards aa points,mainly because of the recent Plat dupe and E-Bayed/Player Auctioned Platinum which has made its way in force to EQ.<br>
<br>
  As soon as I hit 62 I went to bazaar to price my upcoming lvl63 spells only to be knocked on my ass by the sudden massive price increase.KEI went down to 5-7k finally as of October '03.Then when the Platinum dupe hit it skyrocketed back up to over 16k - this happened in less than a week.<br>
<br>
VoQ went from 20k to 80k.HoV from 30k to well over 100k.Spells werent the only item hit and yes I do have sympathy for the tanks who were saving for the Scepter of Destruction which went from 80k to almost 500k in 3 days.<br>
<br>
Who is the real criminal here though?The sellers who saw they CAN sell those items for that price because people had the pp for it courtesy of E-Bay/PA? The buyers for screwing the economy up by illegally purchasing PP with real money out of game to buy the things they are too lazy to go get in game?Or perhaps SOE for not finding better ways to clamp down on the Plat sellers and buyers who are screwing up the honest people in EQ ?<br>
<br>
 My suggestion in my first post was not made primarily as a joke,my suggestion of a strike within EQ.If all casters whom were constantly placed in a position to cast beneficial spells upon others,suddenly and without warning stopped casting,EQ would almost certainly come to a stop.Almost meaning of course these very same people would be expected to buff people in thier own guilds,but no-one else beyond that.<br>
<br>
Lower level toons would be without Temp,C1,etc.Leveling becomes harder and much slower.Higher level toons would be more affected without of course KEI,HoV,Fo7,etc.<br>
<br>
Think how in demand clerics would be if none would join up in LDoN pick-up groups.How in demand chanters would become for that pre-adventure KEI and SoV.How in demend Shamans would be to slow mobs and buff groups.<br>
<br>
My point is one person doing this is like a sparrow all alone in the forest singing - no one hears the one little sparrow singing or they tend to ignore it.However,when that one little sparrow is joined by 3-4-10 thousand more sparrows,then they get noticed and quickly.<br>
<br>
Casters going on a form of strike in EQ would gain not only the attention of the players who need those buffs to survive or make thier game-play easy,it would gain the attention of SOE as well and they might finally hear our plea to make high level spells available on vendors.Would you rather consider going to E-Bay or Player Auction like so many others,just to purchase 250kpp with even MORE money than you are currently paying per month,or would you rather have the option of paying 2-3-4k for the spell off a vendor?<br>
<br>
The simplicity behind this is amazing if anyone in thier right mind stopped for a moment to think about it.And the reaction on SOE's part would I imagine be swift in meeting the demands of they casters who buff others to make thier gameplay easier.<br>
<br>
Of course you will have several who will rant and rave and claim they are going to start thier own chanters,shamans,and clerics just to foil the plans of the people striking,BUT,where will these people get the money to outfit new toons?Where will they get the buffs needed to keep these new toons alive to reach the levels needed for KEI,HoV,and Fo7?Believe me thier journey to uberness will be long and difficult and the people striking will get what they asked for long before these toons reach 60+.<br>
<br>
The answer is simple,go to Sony Online and start sending requests that higher level spells be made available on vendors,even if those vendors are placed in remote,out of the way places and they spell cost was made affordable but high for the honest people who play this game.Not to leave out the melee and hybrids,thier equipment (or at least some equipment) should be made available as well.<br>
<br>
If not on sale from vendors,my opinion is spells that are 60+ might be made no-drop or quested.This would solve the problems of the lvl 65 warrior wearing 500k of gear winning a roll on a spell scroll of VoQ,when there might be a chanter in that very group who needs it.<br>
<br>
Take 5-10 minutes after reading this post and write to SOE voicing your concerns over the high prices,and the inability on the part of honest players to continue leveling because of the E-Bayed/PA platinum making its way into the game.Sony Online Entertainment despite the feelings of many does concern itself with the people who play thier games.If the players are unhappy and they threaten to quit,SOE stands the chance of losing a lot of money.It worked for the warriors who banded together over the aggro problems they have,and SOE was swift to act in order to keep these people from in-game-striking.When one person threatens to quit,SOE is losing only $13 a month.But when 10,000 threaten to quit,IT HURTS THIER WALLETS.<br>
<br>
Of the 450,000 EQ players,I know for certain there are at LEAST 10,000 who have casters.SOE will not take the chance of losing $130,000+ a month. <p>Glaeken Rasilom<br>
Enchanter<br>
